Around 5000 years ago, a group of Stone Age farmers began work on the most astonishing structure in Neolithic Europe. The task would take them one and a half millennia to complete.

How did they move and raise the gigantic blocks that make up Stonehenge's celebrated circle? And what did the alignments of the stones, which track the Sun and Moon with pinpoint precision, really signify?
